            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-07T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-07T15:00:00-05:00" n="1206" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1206">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">865.7962/6–345: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-07T16:00:00-04:00">June 7, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>956. Reurtel 1500 June 3. Question of resumption of commercial air services by
                    Italy still under consideration. If matter still undecided when our air services
                    are ready to operate into Italy we would hope to get unilateral landing rights
                    on an interim basis at least, but in meantime Dept believes it inadvisable to
                    suggest interim agreement to Ital Govt due to implications of reciprocity.
                    Airport matter (your 1353 May 19) being explored by War Dept.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
